How can I write a JavaScript function to find the state that meets the following criteria: it is ranked 5th by area among the states in the United States of America, it is located in the western half of the country, and it is the largest state by area? 
Here is the data for the states in the United States of America in a JavaScript object format:
const states = [
  {
    name: "Alaska",
    area: 1723337,
    region: "West"
  },
  {
    name: "Texas",
    area: 695662,
    region: "South"
  },
  {
    name: "California",
    area: 423972,
    region: "West"
  },
  {
    name: "Montana",
